<h2>ABOUT</h2>
<h3>Collingwood &mdash; A History</h3>
<p>Collingwood real estate was first established in 1959 after the area itself came under Calgary in 1910. The neighborhood is represented by the Ward 7 Councilor at the Calgary City Council.</p>
<p>Collingwood is a residential area located in northwest Calgary. It is situated to the south of John Laurie Boulevard and Nose Hill Park and to the west of 14th Street W. The Confederation Park borders the neighborhood on the south, along with the Confederation Golf Course and the Canmore Park.</p>
<h3>Demographics</h3>
<p>The demographics for Collingwood indicate a population of a bit over 2000 residing within around 1000 dwellings according to the municipal census of 2012. In 2011, the census showed a population of 2,231, indicating a 0.4% increase in the successive year.</p>
<p>The overall land area for Collingwood is roughly 1.6 square kilometers, while population density is measured to be 1,390 per square kilometer. Around 15% of the Collingwood homes are composed of apartment and condominiums, with around 30% of the houses being rented out.</p>
